{"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDate"},{"type":"text","text":" is a struct for calendrical calculations."}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateProtocol","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"],"type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To","kind":"relationships"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef"},"kind":"symbol","topicSections":[{"anchor":"Initializers","title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(_:)-15l2w","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(_:)-5vh9g","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(_:)-6v7fp","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(_:)-7pk3a","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(_:)-9375e","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(constPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(dmy:month:year:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(julian:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(mutating:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(opaquePointer:)"],"generated":true},{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/ptr"],"anchor":"Instance-Properties","title":"Instance Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/new(dmy:month:year:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/new(julian:)"],"anchor":"Type-Methods","title":"Type Methods","generated":true},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/DateProtocol-Implementations","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/PointerWrapper-Implementations"],"title":"Default Implementations","generated":true,"anchor":"Default-Implementations"}],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"DateRef","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib7DateRefV","symbolKind":"struct","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"DateRef"}],"roleHeading":"Structure","title":"DateRef","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DateRef"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GDate","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" data structure represents a day between January 1, Year 1,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and sometime a few thousand years in the future (right now it will go"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to the year 65535 or so, but [method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.Date.set_parse","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] only parses up to the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"year 8000 or so - just count on “a few thousand”). "},{"code":"GDate","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is meant to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"represent everyday dates, not astronomical dates or historical dates","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"or ISO timestamps or the like. It extrapolates the current Gregorian","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"calendar forward and backward in time; there is no attempt to change","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the calendar to match time periods or locations. ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDate"},{"text":" does not store","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"time information; it represents a day.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GDate","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" implementation has several nice features; it is only a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"64-bit struct, so storing large numbers of dates is very efficient. It"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can keep both a Julian and day-month-year representation of the date,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"since some calculations are much easier with one representation or the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"other. A Julian representation is simply a count of days since some"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"fixed day in the past; for ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date"},{"type":"text","text":" the fixed day is January 1, 1 AD."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(“Julian” dates in the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" API aren’t really Julian dates in the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"technical sense; technically, Julian dates count from the start of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Julian period, Jan 1, 4713 BC)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDate"},{"text":" is simple to use. First you need a “blank” date; you can get a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"dynamically allocated date from [ctor","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Date.new"},{"type":"text","text":"], or you can declare an"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"automatic variable or array and initialize it by calling [method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.Date.clear","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"A cleared date is safe; it’s safe to call [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Date.set_dmy"},{"text":"] and the other","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"mutator functions to initialize the value of a cleared date. However, a cleared date","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is initially invalid, meaning that it doesn’t represent a day that exists."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It is undefined to call any of the date calculation routines on an invalid date."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"If you obtain a date from a user or other unpredictable source, you should check"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"its validity with the [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Date.valid"},{"text":"] predicate. [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Date.valid"},{"text":"]","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is also used to check for errors with [method"},{"code":"GLib.Date.set_parse","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] and other functions"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that can fail. Dates can be invalidated by calling [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Date.clear"},{"type":"text","text":"] again."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is very important to use the API to access the "},{"code":"GDate","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct. Often only the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"day-month-year or only the Julian representation is valid. Sometimes neither is valid."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use the API."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"GLib also features "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDateTime"},{"text":" which represents a precise time.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef","type":"reference"},{"text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDate"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef"},{"text":" only as an ","type":"text"},{"code":"unowned","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" reference to an existing ","type":"text"},{"code":"GDate","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]},{"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" (instead of ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDate"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/dateref"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateRef/init(_:)-9375e":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Designated initialiser from a constant pointer to the underlying "},{"code":"C","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" data type","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/dateref\/init(_:)-9375e","role":"symbol","title":"init(_:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(_:)-9375e","fragments":[{"text":"init","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(",